# Inventory Service Mirrord Workflow

Use this rule whenever changing `apps/shop/inventory-service` or product catalogue API behavior.
Verify against the live playground cluster with mirrord filtered traffic before reporting the change as done.

## Target

- Service path: `apps/shop/inventory-service`
- Kubernetes deployment: `deploy/inventory-service`
- Namespace: `shop`
- mirrord config: `apps/shop/inventory-service/mirrord.json`
- Public shop URL: `https://playground.metalbear.dev/shop`
- Shop visualization: `https://playground.metalbear.dev/visualization-shop`

## Before Running

From the repo root, confirm the cluster and target:

```bash
mirrord --version
kubectl config current-context
kubectl -n shop get deploy inventory-service
```

The expected kube context is:

```text
gke_playground-383912_us-central1-c_playground-cluster-1
```

Do not continue against an unexpected cluster.

## Run Inventory Locally With Filtered Traffic

Use a stable session key and run inventory-service under mirrord:

```bash
export MIRRORD_SESSION="${MIRRORD_SESSION:-${USER:-cursor-inventory}}"
USER="$MIRRORD_SESSION" \
  mirrord exec -f apps/shop/inventory-service/mirrord.json -- \
  npm --prefix apps/shop/inventory-service run dev
```

`mirrord.json` steals only HTTP requests whose `baggage` header contains:

```text
mirrord-session=<MIRRORD_SESSION>
```

Do not remove or widen the `http_filter` to make a test pass.

## Send Filtered Test Traffic

In another shell, send traffic through the public user-facing shop URL with the matching baggage
header. This must exercise the gateway, `metal-mart-frontend`, its product API route, and then
`inventory-service`.

```bash
export MIRRORD_SESSION="${MIRRORD_SESSION:-${USER:-cursor-inventory}}"
curl -sS \
  -H "baggage: mirrord-session=${MIRRORD_SESSION}" \
  https://playground.metalbear.dev/shop/api/products
```

The request must appear in the local inventory-service logs. Also send an unfiltered request and confirm
it does not hit the local process:

```bash
curl -sS https://playground.metalbear.dev/shop/api/products
```

## HTTP Checks

Use only public shop endpoints for mirrord verification:

```bash
# List products
curl -sS \
  -H "baggage: mirrord-session=${MIRRORD_SESSION}" \
  https://playground.metalbear.dev/shop/api/products

# Single product
curl -sS \
  -H "baggage: mirrord-session=${MIRRORD_SESSION}" \
  https://playground.metalbear.dev/shop/api/products/1
```

For UI-level verification, use Playwright or a browser with the same request header and navigate to
`https://playground.metalbear.dev/shop/products` or the product page affected by the change. In
Playwright, set the header on the browser context:

```ts
const context = await browser.newContext({
  extraHTTPHeaders: {
    baggage: `mirrord-session=${process.env.MIRRORD_SESSION}`,
  },
});
```

Never use `http://inventory-service/...`, a port-forward, or an in-cluster curl pod as the primary
verification path for inventory-service changes. The demo must go through the same public path a user
uses.

## Header Forwarding Requirement

The public product API route must forward the incoming `baggage` header when it calls
`inventory-service`; otherwise the inventory-service mirrord filter will never see the session key.
If the filtered public request does not reach the local inventory-service, inspect and fix the relevant
frontend proxy route under `apps/shop/metal-mart-frontend/src/app/api/products*/` before changing the
mirrord filter.

## Completion Criteria

- `npm --prefix apps/shop/inventory-service run build` or `npm --prefix apps/shop/inventory-service run lint` passes.
- A filtered request to `https://playground.metalbear.dev/shop/api/products...` with `baggage: mirrord-session=<MIRRORD_SESSION>` reaches the local service.
- An unfiltered request to the same public endpoint does not reach the local service.
- The changed inventory behavior is verified through the public shop path and the local mirrord process.
